destruction of newly paved roads, the State Road Commission shall provide to the Public Service Commission notice of planned utility maintenance, construction, and repairs at least 30 calendar days prior to the planned start date of the paving or construction project on state roads.(b) In the event that a utility project is scheduled that will require digging or cutting of the roads that the State Road Commission has planned to pave or perform extensive construction, the State Road shall reschedule to paving or construction project for after the completion of the utility project's completion.(c) Nothing in this section or §24-9-1 shall be construed to prohibit the State Road Commission from filling potholes or performing other necessary maintenance for the safety of automotive and foot traffic upon these roads that are scheduled for utility projects under the Public Service Commission. chapter 24. public service commission. article 9. paving and Scheduled Maintenance of utilities. §24-9-1. Utility maintenance and paving conflicts. (a) In order to avoid the expense and destruction of newly paved roads, the State Road Commission shall provide to the Public Service Commission notice of planned utility maintenance, construction, and repairs at least 30 calendar days prior to the planned start date of the paving or construction project on state roads.(b) The Public Service Commission shall notify the State Road Commission at least 15 calendar days prior to the start date of the scheduled paving or other maintenance project if there is a scheduled utility project that will dig up, cut through, or otherwise damage the roads planned to be paved or otherwise constructed upon.(c) In the event that a utility project is scheduled that will require digging or cutting of the roads that the State Road Commission has planned to pave or perform extensive construction, the State Road shall reschedule to paving or construction project for after the completion of the utility project's completion.(d) Nothing in this section or §17-31-1 shall be construed to prohibit the State Road Commission from filling potholes or performing other necessary maintenance for the safety of automotive and foot traffic upon these roads that are scheduled for utility projects under the Public Service Commission. NOTE: The purpose of this bill is to require all paving projects to be approved by the Public Service Commission in order to prevent the digging up of newly paved roads for planned utility projects.Strike-throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law and underscoring indicates new language that would be added. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone: